{
  "text": "Ischemic stroke, however, is a disease that is directly related to age, and the prevalence of ischemic stroke has been reported to nearly double in patients over the age of 65 among all ethnicities. [CITATION_1] As more were conservatively managed, concluded that both survival and functional outcome was significantly improved in the decompressive craniectomy group. [CITATION_2] In the current series, many of the findings coincided with previous studies, yet we also noticed some striking disparities.",
